Chi-Square Test

2=(OE)2E2=(OE)2E

  • O=O= observed frequency

  • E=E= Expected frequency

  • Sum across cells.

Degrees of Freedom for One Variable:

df=k1df=k1

k=k= Number of categories.


Expected Frequencies for Two Variables:

Eij=RiCjNEij=RiCjN

  • R = row total
  • C = Column total

Degrees of Freedom for Two Variables:

df=(R1)(C1)df=(R1)(C1)

  • R = Number of rows in the table.
  • C = Number of columns in the table.



Miscellaneous

MAD-Median Rule:

|Xmedian(x)|MADN>2.24|Xmedian(x)|MADN>2.24


Biserial Correlation:

Rb=RpbpquRb=Rpbpqu

  • Rpb=Rpb= Point-Biseral Correlation.
  • p=p= Proportion of cases falling into the largest category.
  • q=q= Proportion of cases falling into the smallest category.

  • u=u= the ordinate (i.e., y-axis value) of a standard normal distribution at pp.

  • Standard Error: SRb=pquNSRb=pquN

  • Test Statistic: ZRb=RbbSRbZRb=RbbSRb
